            "creation_date": 1571393465,
            "body": "<p>If you simply want your API call to create a new Article, how about simply having a <code>PostMapping<\/code> to <code>/article/new<\/code> (for example) and then simply pass the new Article's parameters as RequestBody?<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>@PostMapping(\"article/new\")\npublic ResponseEntity&lt;Void&gt; addArticle(@RequestBody Article article) {\n// ...\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Then as RequestBody you would have something like:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>{ \"param1\": \"value1\", \"param2\": \"value2\", \"param3\": \"value3\" }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>If you're just looking to include more PathVariable's to your api call, refer to @sovannarith cheav's answer<\/p>\n\n<p>I hope this helps<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 58448690,
            "question_id": 58447860,
            "last_edit_date": 1571393937
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-PorxuWBrhWQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAvQ/vQxknro2JnM/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
                "account_id": 14374791,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 10383493,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10383493/sovannarith-cheav",
                "reputation": 793,
                "display_name": "sovannarith cheav"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1571393040,
            "creation_date": 1571393040,
            "body": "<blockquote>\n  <p>Is there a way to expand the code model from below to 3 parameters? headers.setLocation(builder.path(\"/article/{param1}/{param2}/{param3}\")<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>You can use <a href=\"https://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/web/bind/annotation/PathVariable.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">@PathVariable<\/a>, like below<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>@PostMapping(\"article/{param1}/{param2}/{param3}\")\npublic ResponseEntity&lt;Void&gt; addArticle(@PathVariable(\"param1\") String param1, @PathVariable(\"param3\") String param3, @PathVariable(\"param3\") String param3) {\n    //enter code here\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
